==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Destructionist
<hw>De*struc"tion*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
delights in destroying that which is valuable; one whose principles and
influence tend to destroy existing institutions; a
destructive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>One who believes in the final
destruction or complete annihilation of the wicked; -- called also
<altname>annihilationist</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Destructive</ent>⟦br⟧
